INSERT INTO `histab` VALUES (1,'Taj Mahal','Agra, Uttar Pradesh','Built by Mughal Emperor Shah Jahan in memory of his wife Mumtaz Mahal.','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/1.jpg','The Taj Mahal is an ivory-white marble mausoleum on the right bank of the river Yamuna in the Indian city of Agra. It was commissioned in 1632 by the Mughal emperor Shah Jahan to house the tomb of his favourite wife, Mumtaz Mahal; it also houses the tomb of Shah Jahan himself. The Taj Mahal was designated as a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 1983 for being \"the jewel of Muslim art in India and one of the universally admired masterpieces of the world\'s heritage\".','1632 - 1653','Mughal, Islamic, Persian, Indian','Marble, Red sandstone, Precious stones','(27.1751,78.0421)'),(2,'Qutub Minar','New Delhi','The tallest minaret in the world made of bricks.','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/2.jpg','Qutub Minar is a minaret and \"victory tower\" that forms part of the Qutb complex, a UNESCO World Heritage Site in the Mehrauli area of Delhi, India. It is the tallest minaret in the world made up of bricks and has a height of 73 meters (240 feet). Construction commenced in 1192 under the orders of India\'s first Muslim ruler, Qutb-ud-din Aibak, and was completed by his successor, Iltutmish.','1193 - 1369','Indo-Islamic, Mughal','Red sandstone, Marble','(28.5245,77.1855)'),(3,'Hampi','Hampi, Karnataka','Historical city and UNESCO World Heritage Site known for its ruins.','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/3.jpg','Hampi, also referred to as the Group of Monuments at Hampi, is a UNESCO World Heritage Site located in east-central Karnataka, India. It was the capital of the Vijayanagara Empire in the 14th century and is known for its well-preserved ruins, temples, and monuments, which include the Virupaksha Temple, Vittala Temple, and Hampi Bazaar. The ruins at Hampi are spread over a vast area and attract tourists and history enthusiasts from around the world.','14th - 16th century','Vijayanagara','Granite, Schist, Sandstone','(15.3350,76.4621)'),(4,'Ajanta Caves','Aurangabad, Maharashtra','Rock-cut Buddhist cave monuments.','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/4.jpg','The Ajanta Caves are a series of rock-cut Buddhist cave monuments located in Aurangabad district of Maharashtra, India. The caves date back to the 2nd century BCE and were used by Buddhist monks as prayer halls and monastic retreats. They are renowned for their exquisite frescoes, sculptures, and architectural features, which depict scenes from the life of Buddha and various Jataka tales.','2nd century BCE - 6th century CE','Buddhist, Indian, Rock-cut','Rock-cut, Stone','(20.5525,75.7030)'),(5,'Red Fort','New Delhi','Historic fort complex built by Mughal Emperor Shah Jahan.','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/5.jpg','The Red Fort, also known as Lal Qila, is a historic fort complex located in the heart of Old Delhi, India. It was built by the Mughal Emperor Shah Jahan in the 17th century as the main residence of the Mughal emperors. The fort is made of red sandstone and is known for its impressive architecture, including the Diwan-i-Am (Hall of Public Audience), Diwan-i-Khas (Hall of Private Audience), and the iconic Moti Masjid (Pearl Mosque). The Red Fort is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and is a symbol of India\'s rich cultural heritage.','1638 - 1648','Mughal','Red sandstone, Marble','(28.6562,77.2410)'),(6,'Khajuraho Group of Monuments','Khajuraho, Madhya Pradesh','Famous for its Hindu and Jain temples, known for their erotic sculptures.','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/6.jpg','The Khajuraho Group of Monuments is a UNESCO World Heritage Site located in the Chhatarpur district of Madhya Pradesh, India. It comprises a group of Hindu and Jain temples, known for their intricate and ornate erotic sculptures. The temples were built between the 9th and 12th centuries by the Chandela dynasty and represent one of the finest examples of temple architecture in India.','950 - 1050','Hindu, Jain','Sandstone','(24.8318,79.9199)'),(7,'Ellora Caves','Aurangabad, Maharashtra','Rock-cut cave complexes featuring Buddhist, Hindu, and Jain temples.','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/7.jpg','The Ellora Caves are a UNESCO World Heritage Site located near the city of Aurangabad in Maharashtra, India. The caves consist of rock-cut temples and monasteries carved into the Charanandri hills and date back to the 6th and 9th centuries. The caves represent a unique blend of Hindu, Buddhist, and Jain architecture and are renowned for their exquisite carvings and sculptures.','6th - 10th century','Buddhist, Hindu, Jain, Rock-cut','Basalt rock','(20.0269,75.1773)'),(8,'Agra Fort','Agra, Uttar Pradesh','A historical fort in the city of Agra.','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/8.jpg','Agra Fort is a UNESCO World Heritage Site located in Agra, Uttar Pradesh, India. It was built by the Mughal Emperor Akbar in the 16th century and served as the main residence of the Mughal emperors until the capital was shifted to Delhi. The fort is made of red sandstone and encompasses palaces, mosques, and gardens, including the famous Jahangir Palace and Khas Mahal.','1565 - 1573','Mughal','Red sandstone','(27.1795,78.0212)'),(9,'Sanchi Stupa','Sanchi, Madhya Pradesh','Buddhist complex, including stupas, monasteries, temples, and pillars.','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/9.jpg','The Sanchi Stupa is a Buddhist complex located near the town of Sanchi in Madhya Pradesh, India. It is one of the oldest stone structures in India and dates back to the 3rd century BCE. The stupa was commissioned by the Mauryan Emperor Ashoka and is adorned with intricate carvings depicting scenes from the life of Buddha. The Sanchi Stupa is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and is considered one of the most important Buddhist monuments in the world.','3rd century BCE - 12th century CE','Buddhist, Stupa','Stone, Brick','(23.4821,77.7381)'),(10,'Konark Sun Temple','Konark, Odisha','A UNESCO World Heritage Site, dedicated to the Hindu Sun God Surya.','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/10.jpg','The Konark Sun Temple is a UNESCO World Heritage Site located in the town of Konark in Odisha, India. Dedicated to the Hindu Sun God Surya, the temple was built in the 13th century by King Narasimhadeva I of the Eastern Ganga Dynasty. The temple is known for its intricate stone carvings and unique architectural style, which resembles a colossal chariot with wheels, drawn by seven horses.','13th century','Kalinga, Kalingan','Sandstone','(19.8876,86.0928)'),(11,'Mysore Palace','Mysore, Karnataka','Palace located in Mysore, Karnataka','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/11.jpg','Mysore Palace, also known as the Amba Vilas Palace, is a historic palace located in the city of Mysore in Karnataka, India. It was originally built in the 14th century and underwent several renovations and expansions over the centuries. The palace is known for its Indo-Saracenic architecture, with influences from Hindu, Muslim, Rajput, and Gothic styles. It is one of the most famous tourist attractions in Mysore and is illuminated with thousands of lights during the Dasara festival.','1897 - 1912','Indo-Saracenic, Hindu','Grey granite, Marble','(12.3051,76.6551)'),(12,'Meenakshi Temple','Madurai, Tamil Nadu','Historic Hindu temple dedicated to Meenakshi and Sundareswarar deities','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/12.jpg','Meenakshi Temple is a historic Hindu temple located in the city of Madurai in Tamil Nadu, India. Dedicated to the goddess Meenakshi, the temple complex is one of the largest and most important pilgrimage sites in India. It is known for its towering gopurams (gateway towers), intricately carved sculptures, and vibrant colors. The temple attracts millions of devotees and tourists every year.','16th - 17th century','Dravidian','Granite, Sandstone','(9.9195,78.1193)'),(13,'Brihadeeswarar Temple','Thanjavur, Tamil Nadu','One of the largest temples in India, dedicated to Lord Shiva','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/13.jpg','Brihadeeswarar Temple, also known as the Big Temple, is a Hindu temple dedicated to Lord Shiva located in Thanjavur, Tamil Nadu, India. Built by the Chola dynasty in the 11th century, it is one of the largest temples in India and is renowned for its magnificent architecture and towering vimana (temple tower). The temple is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and is considered a masterpiece of Dravidian architecture.','1003 - 1010','Dravidian','Granite','(10.7828,79.1317)'),(14,'Sree Padmanabhaswamy Temple','Thiruvananthapuram, Kerala','Hindu temple known for its architectural beauty and deity Vishnu','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/14.jpg','Sree Padmanabhaswamy Temple is a Hindu temple located in Thiruvananthapuram, the capital city of Kerala, India. Dedicated to Lord Vishnu, the temple is known for its stunning Dravidian architecture and is considered one of the 108 Divya Desams (holy abodes of Vishnu). The temples main deity, Padmanabhaswamy, is depicted in a reclining posture on the serpent Ananta Shesha.','8th century','Dravidian, Kerala','Granite, Stone','(8.4839,76.9493)'),(15,'Mattancherry Palace','Kochi, Kerala','Former royal palace with a museum exhibiting Kerala murals and artifacts','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/15.jpg','Mattancherry Palace, also known as the Dutch Palace, is a Portuguese palace located in the Mattancherry neighborhood of Kochi, Kerala, India. Built in the 16th century, the palace showcases Kerala-style architecture and features a central courtyard, traditional Kerala murals, and portraits of the Cochin royal family. The palace is now a museum and is known for its historical and cultural significance.','1555','Portuguese, Kerala','Laterite, Wood','(9.9575,76.2421)'),(16,'Bekal Fort','Kasaragod, Kerala','Historic fort overlooking the Arabian Sea, built in the 17th century','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/16.jpg','Bekal Fort is a historic fort located in the Kasaragod district of Kerala, India. Situated on the Arabian Sea coast, the fort dates back to the 17th century and offers panoramic views of the surrounding landscape. It is one of the largest and best-preserved forts in Kerala and is a popular tourist destination.','17th century','Mughal, Kerala','Laterite stones','(12.3702,75.0366)'),(17,'Guruvayur Temple','Thrissur, Kerala','One of the most sacred Hindu temples dedicated to Lord Krishna','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/17.jpg','Guruvayur Temple is a Hindu temple dedicated to Lord Krishna located in the town of Guruvayur in Kerala, India. It is one of the most sacred and important temples in Kerala and is known for its unique rituals and festivals. The temple attracts millions of devotees every year and is renowned for its serene atmosphere and divine aura.','1638','Kerala, Hindu','Laterite, Granite','(10.5941,76.0463)'),(18,'Chettinad Palace','Chettinad, Tamil Nadu','Historic mansion showcasing Chettinad architecture and culture','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/18.jpg','Chettinad Palace is a historic mansion located in the Chettinad region of Tamil Nadu, India. Built by the wealthy Chettiar community in the early 20th century, the palace showcases Chettinad architecture and design elements, including intricately carved wooden doors, stained glass windows, and decorative tiles. It is a fine example of South Indian heritage and craftsmanship.','19th century','Chettinad, Tamil Nadu','Wood, Teak, Athangudi tiles','(10.4035,78.8113)'),(19,'Dutch Palace','Kochi, Kerala','Historical palace known for its Kerala murals and portraits of Dutch colonial governors','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/19.jpg','Dutch Palace, also known as Mattancherry Palace, is a Portuguese palace located in Kochi, Kerala, India. Built in the 16th century, the palace features Kerala-style architecture and is known for its exquisite murals depicting Hindu mythology, scenes from the Ramayana and Mahabharata, and portraits of the Cochin royal family. It is a popular tourist attraction and is managed by the Archaeological Survey of India.','1555','Portuguese, Kerala','Wood, Laterite','(9.9667,76.2422)'),(20,'Jantar Mantar','Jaipur, Rajasthan','Astronomical observatory with architectural instruments for celestial measurements','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/20.jpg','Jantar Mantar is an astronomical observatory located in Jaipur, Rajasthan, India. Built by Maharaja Jai Singh II in the early 18th century, it consists of a collection of architectural astronomical instruments designed to measure time, predict eclipses, and observe celestial bodies. The observatory is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and is one of the largest and best-preserved observatories in the world.','1727 - 1734','Hindu, Astronomy','Stone, Marble','(26.9249,75.8245)'),(21,'Mehrangarh Fort','Jodhpur, Rajasthan','One of the largest forts in India, housing palaces and a museum','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/21.jpg','Mehrangarh Fort is a historic fort located in Jodhpur, Rajasthan, India. Built around 1460 by Rao Jodha, the fort is situated on a rocky hill overlooking the city. It is one of the largest forts in India and houses several palaces, galleries, and a museum. The fort\'s imposing walls and intricate architecture make it a popular tourist attraction.','1459','Rajput','Red sandstone','(26.2985,73.0181)'),(22,'Hawa Mahal','Jaipur, Rajasthan','Iconic palace known for its honeycomb-like facade and windows','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/22.jpg','Hawa Mahal, also known as the Palace of Winds, is a unique five-story palace located in Jaipur, Rajasthan, India. Built in 1799 by Maharaja Sawai Pratap Singh, the palace is renowned for its honeycomb-like facade with 953 small windows (jharokhas) designed to allow royal ladies to observe street festivals while remaining unseen from the outside. It is an iconic symbol of Jaipur\'s architectural heritage.','1799','Rajput','Red and pink sandstone','(26.9239,75.8267)'),(23,'Victoria Memorial','Kolkata, West Bengal','Monument built in memory of Queen Victoria, now a museum','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/23.jpg','Victoria Memorial is a grand marble building located in Kolkata, West Bengal, India. Built between 1906 and 1921, the memorial honors Queen Victoria and houses a museum showcasing artifacts, paintings, and sculptures from the British colonial period. Surrounded by lush gardens, the Victoria Memorial is one of Kolkata\'s most prominent landmarks and a popular tourist destination.','1906 - 1921','Indo-Saracenic','Marble','(22.5448,88.3426)'),(24,'Golconda Fort','Hyderabad, Telangana','Ancient fort known for its acoustics and architecture','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/24.jpg','Golconda Fort is a historic fort located in Hyderabad, Telangana, India. Dating back to the 12th century, the fort was originally built by the Kakatiya dynasty and later expanded by the Qutb Shahi kings. It is renowned for its impressive architecture, acoustic design, and diamond mines. Golconda Fort offers panoramic views of the surrounding landscape and is a popular tourist attraction.','1143','Mughal, Persian','Granite, Mud bricks','(17.3833,78.4044)'),(25,'Charminar','Hyderabad, Telangana','Iconic monument and mosque with four minarets','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/25.jpg','Charminar is a historic monument and mosque located in Hyderabad, Telangana, India. Built in 1591 by Sultan Muhammad Quli Qutb Shah, the Charminar is known for its distinctive four minarets and intricate Islamic architecture. It is a symbol of Hyderabad\'s rich cultural heritage and serves as a popular landmark and gathering place.','1591','Indo-Islamic','Granite, Lime mortar','(17.3616,78.4747)'),(26,'Amer Fort','Jaipur, Rajasthan','Historic fort overlooking Maota Lake, known for its grandeur and architecture','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/26.jpg','Amer Fort, also known as Amber Fort, is a majestic fortress located in Amer, near Jaipur, Rajasthan, India. Built in the 16th century by Raja Man Singh I, the fort showcases a blend of Rajput and Mughal architectural styles. It features stunning palaces, courtyards, and a series of gates, including the imposing Ganesh Pol and the Sheesh Mahal (Hall of Mirrors).','1592 - 1599','Rajput','Red sandstone, Marble','(26.9855,75.8513)'),(27,'Humayun\'s Tomb','New Delhi','Mughal emperor Humayun\'s tomb, an early example of Mughal architecture in India','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/27.jpg','Humayun\'s Tomb is a UNESCO World Heritage Site located in New Delhi, India. Built in the mid-16th century, the tomb is the final resting place of the Mughal emperor Humayun. It is renowned for its elegant Mughal architecture, including its distinctive red sandstone facade, marble dome, and expansive gardens. Humayun\'s Tomb is considered a precursor to the Taj Mahal.','1565','Mughal','Red sandstone, Marble','(28.5933,77.2507)'),(28,'Mughal Gardens','New Delhi','Prestigious gardens surrounding the Rashtrapati Bhavan, open to the public in spring','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/28.jpg','Mughal Gardens are a group of gardens located within the Rashtrapati Bhavan complex in New Delhi, India. Designed by Sir Edwin Lutyens, the gardens are inspired by the traditional Mughal style of landscaping. They feature terraced lawns, flower beds, water channels, and symmetrical pathways, creating a serene and picturesque environment. The Mughal Gardens are open to the public during the annual Udyanotsav festival.','1917 - 1929','Mughal','Marble, Red sandstone','(28.6143,77.1996)'),(29,'India Gate','New Delhi','War memorial dedicated to soldiers who died in World War I, located in the heart of Delhi','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/29.jpg','India Gate is a war memorial located in the heart of New Delhi, India. Built in memory of the Indian soldiers who died in World War I, the monument is an iconic symbol of national pride and sacrifice. Surrounding the gate is the Amar Jawan Jyoti (the eternal flame), which serves as a tribute to the Unknown Soldier. India Gate is a popular destination for locals and tourists alike.','1921 - 1931','Colonial','Red sandstone, Granite','(28.6129,77.2295)'),(30,'Fatehpur Sikri','Fatehpur Sikri, Uttar Pradesh','Historical city built by Emperor Akbar, known for its architecture and monuments','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/30.jpg','Fatehpur Sikri is a UNESCO World Heritage Site located near Agra, Uttar Pradesh, India. Built in the 16th century by Emperor Akbar, the city served as the capital of the Mughal Empire for a brief period. It is renowned for its well-preserved red sandstone buildings, including palaces, mosques, and courtyards. Fatehpur Sikri is a masterpiece of Mughal architecture and is visited by thousands of tourists each year.','1571 - 1585','Mughal','Red sandstone','(27.0945,77.6677)'),(31,'Jaisalmer Fort','Jaisalmer, Rajasthan','Golden fort in the heart of the Thar Desert, known for its sandstone architecture','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/31.jpg','Jaisalmer Fort is a historic fort located in the city of Jaisalmer, Rajasthan, India. Built in 1156 by Rawal Jaisal, the fort stands atop Trikuta Hill and is made of yellow sandstone, giving it a golden hue. It is one of the largest fully preserved fortified cities in the world and houses palaces, temples, and residential complexes. Jaisalmer Fort is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and a popular tourist destination.','1156','Rajput','Yellow sandstone','(26.9179,70.9077)'),(32,'Udaipur City Palace','Udaipur, Rajasthan','Magnificent palace complex overlooking Lake Pichola, housing museums and courtyards','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/32.jpg','Udaipur City Palace is a magnificent palace complex located on the banks of Lake Pichola in Udaipur, Rajasthan, India. Built over several centuries, the palace showcases a blend of Rajput and Mughal architectural styles. It features ornate palaces, courtyards, gardens, and a museum displaying royal artifacts and portraits. Udaipur City Palace is one of the most visited attractions in Udaipur and offers panoramic views of the lake and surrounding hills.','1559','Rajput, Mughal','Marble, Granite','(24.5765,73.6835)'),(33,'Rani ki Vav','Patan, Gujarat','Stepwell with intricate carvings dedicated to the queen in the 11th century','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/33.jpg','Rani ki Vav is an intricately designed stepwell located in Patan, Gujarat, India. Built in the 11th century by Queen Udayamati in memory of her husband, King Bhimdev I, the stepwell is a UNESCO World Heritage Site. It features stunning sculptures, carvings, and ornamental work depicting various Hindu deities, celestial beings, and mythological motifs. Rani ki Vav is considered one of the most impressive stepwells in India.','11th century','Solanki','Sandstone','(23.8486,72.1263)'),(34,'Bibi Ka Maqbara','Aurangabad, Maharashtra','Mausoleum built by Aurangzeb in memory of his wife, resembling the Taj Mahal','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/34.jpg','Bibi Ka Maqbara is a mausoleum located in Aurangabad, Maharashtra, India. Built in the late 17th century by Mughal Emperor Aurangzeb as a tribute to his wife, Dilras Banu Begum, the mausoleum resembles the iconic Taj Mahal in Agra. Bibi Ka Maqbara is known for its exquisite Mughal architecture, including its intricately designed marble facade, minarets, and surrounding gardens.','1651 - 1661','Mughal, Deccani','Marble, Stone','(19.8762,75.3433)'),(35,'Chittorgarh Fort','Chittorgarh, Rajasthan','Massive fort complex with palaces, temples, and towers, symbolizing Rajput spirit','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/35.jpg','Chittorgarh Fort is a historic fortress located in the city of Chittorgarh, Rajasthan, India. Built in the 7th century AD by the Maurya dynasty, the fort is perched atop a hill and covers an area of 700 acres. It is renowned for its massive gates, towers, temples, and palaces, including the iconic Vijay Stambh (Victory Tower) and Kirti Stambh (Tower of Fame). Chittorgarh Fort is a UNESCO World Heritage Site.','7th century','Rajput','Stone, Marble','(24.8822,74.6235)'),(36,'Ranthambore Fort','Ranthambore, Rajasthan','Historical fort located within Ranthambore National Park, offering panoramic views','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/36.jpg','Ranthambore Fort is a historic fort located within the Ranthambore National Park in Rajasthan, India. Built in the 10th century, the fort is situated atop a hill and offers panoramic views of the surrounding forests and wildlife. It served as a strategic military fortification and was later converted into a hunting lodge by the Maharajas of Jaipur. Ranthambore Fort is a popular tourist attraction.','10th century','Indian, Rajput','Stone','(26.0269,76.5064)'),(37,'Golkonda Fort','Hyderabad, Telangana','Medieval fort complex known for its acoustic architecture and historical significance','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/37.jpg','Golkonda Fort is a medieval fortification located in Hyderabad, Telangana, India. Built by the Kakatiya dynasty in the 13th century and later expanded by the Qutb Shahi kings, the fort is known for its impressive architecture, acoustic design, and diamond mines. Golkonda Fort offers stunning views of the city and is a popular tourist destination.','1143','Indo-Islamic','Granite, Stone','(17.3833,78.4011)'),(38,'City Palace, Jaipur','Jaipur, Rajasthan','Palace complex with museums, courtyards, and royal residences in the heart of Jaipur','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/38.jpg','City Palace, Jaipur, is a historic palace complex located in the heart of Jaipur, Rajasthan, India. Built in the 18th century by Maharaja Sawai Jai Singh II, the palace showcases a fusion of Rajput, Mughal, and European architectural styles. It houses several courtyards, gardens, museums, and palaces, including the Chandra Mahal and Mubarak Mahal. City Palace, Jaipur, is a symbol of the city\'s royal heritage and cultural richness.','1732 - 1734','Rajput, Mughal, European','Marble, Stone','(26.9255,75.8236)'),(39,'Umaid Bhawan Palace','Jodhpur, Rajasthan','One of the world\'s largest private residences, now partially a museum and luxury hotel','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/39.jpg','Umaid Bhawan Palace is a majestic palace located in Jodhpur, Rajasthan, India. Built in the 20th century by Maharaja Umaid Singh, the palace is one of the largest private residences in the world. It features a blend of Indo-Saracenic, Art Deco, and traditional Rajput architecture. Today, a part of the palace serves as a luxury hotel, while another section houses a museum showcasing the royal history of Jodhpur.','1929 - 1943','Indo-Saracenic, Art Deco, Rajput','Sandstone, Marble','(26.2895,73.0322)'),(40,'Sabarmati Ashram','Ahmedabad, Gujarat','Gandhi\'s ashram and center for India\'s freedom struggle, now a museum and monument','C:/Users/Abhin/Desktop/New folder/New folder/photos/40.jpg','Sabarmati Ashram, also known as Gandhi Ashram, is a historic site located in Ahmedabad, Gujarat, India. Established by Mahatma Gandhi in 1917, the ashram served as his residence and center for the Indian independence movement. It played a significant role in India\'s struggle for freedom and remains a pilgrimage site for admirers of Gandhi. The ashram houses a museum, library, and various artifacts associated with Gandhi\'s life and teachings.','1917','Colonial','Brick, Stone','(2